Text.1335: b'"It is surely the pursuit of peace that is most needed in this world so full of strife." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1336: b'"As members of Congress reflect on their pending decision, I urge them to set aside political considerations.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1337: b'"As Americans, we should be proud of this achievement." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1338: b'"Now we have before us a solution that prevents Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon without resorting to war." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1339: b'"President Kennedy warned Americans not to see conflict as inevitable. It is time to apply such wisdom.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1340: b'"I have repeatedly challenged anyone opposed to this deal to put forward a better, plausible alternative." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1341: b'"When we carefully examine the arguments against this deal, none of them stand up to scrutiny.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1342: b'"If Iran violates this deal, we will have ample opportunity to respond." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1343: b'"Worry less about being labeled weak. Worry more about getting it right.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1344: b'"How can we in good conscience justify war before we have tested a diplomatic agreement that achieves our objectives?" \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1345: b'\xe2\x80\x9cThe choice we face is ultimately between diplomacy or some sort of war.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1346: b'\xe2\x80\x9cWalk away from this agreement and you will get a better deal\xe2\x80\x94for Iran.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1347: b'\xe2\x80\x9cThose who say we can walk away from this deal and maintain sanctions are selling a fantasy.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1348: b'"We will continue to have sanctions in place on Iran\'s support for terrorism and violation of human rights."\xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1349: b"\xe2\x80\x9cThere is no scenario where sanctions relief turns Iran into the region's dominate power.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal"
Text.1350: b'\xe2\x80\x9cAn argument against sanctions relief is effectively an argument against any diplomatic solution.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1351: b'"Without this deal, the scenarios that critics warn about happening in 15 years could happen six months from now." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1352: b'"The bottom line is, if Iran cheats, we can catch them\xe2\x80\x94and we will." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1353: b'\xe2\x80\x9cThis deal is not just the best choice among alternatives\xe2\x80\x94this is the strongest non-proliferation agreement ever.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1354: b'\xe2\x80\x9cIf Iran violates the agreement over the next decade all of the sanctions can snap back in to place.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1355: b'"Iran has powerful incentives to keep its commitments." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1356: b'"This deal shuts off the type of covert program Iran has pursued in the past.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1357: b'"In July, we reached a comprehensive plan of action that meets our objectives." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1358: b'"What was once proclaimed as a historic mistake is now held up as a success." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1359: b"\xe2\x80\x9cThe progress of Iran's nuclear program was halted for the first time in a decade.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal"
Text.1360: b'"It was diplomacy that ratcheted up the pressure on Iran." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1361: b'"Winning this global buy-in was not easy. I know. I was there." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1362: b'"What made our new approach more effective was our ability to draw upon new U.N. Security Council resolutions." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1363: b'\xe2\x80\x9cIt was our very willingness to negotiate that helped America rally the world to our cause.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1364: b'"I have also made clear my preference for a peaceful diplomatic resolution of the issue." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1365: b'"Even before taking office, I made clear that Iran would not be allowed to acquire a nuclear weapon on my watch." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1366: b'"The question then is not whether to prevent Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon, but how." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1367: b'"Now more than ever, we need clear thinking in our foreign policy." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'
Text.1368: b'\xe2\x80\x9cMore than a decade later, we still live with the consequences of the decision to invade Iraq.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #IranDeal'

Text.1428: b'"If we keep taking steps toward a more perfect union ... America will move forward. There\'s nothing we can\'t do." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1429: b'"We cannot ignore the problems that we have, but we can\'t stop running the race." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1430: b'"We are not perfect, but we have the capacity to be more perfect\xe2\x80\x94mile after mile, step after step." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1431: b'"Justice and redemption go hand in hand." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1432: b'"Justice is living up to the common creed that I am my brother\'s keeper and I am my sister\'s keeper." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1433: b'"Justice is making sure that every young person knows that they are special and their lives matter." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1434: b'"Justice is not only the absence of oppression\xe2\x80\x94it is the presence of opportunity." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1435: b'"Let\'s reward prisoners with reduced sentences if they complete programs that make them less likely to repeat an offense." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1436: b'"I\'ve asked my Attorney General to start a review of the overuse of solitary confinement in our federal prisons." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1437: b'"We should not tolerate conditions in prison that have no place in any civilized country." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1438: b'"On Thursday, I will be the first sitting president to visit a federal prison." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1439: b'"We should pass a sentencing reform bill through congress this year." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1440: b'"For nonviolent drug crimes, we need to lower long mandatory minimum sentences\xe2\x80\x94or get rid of them entirely." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1441: b'"Don\'t just tag them as future criminals. Reach out to them as future citizens." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1442: b'"We have to restore trust between our police and some of the communities where they serve." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1443: b'"We gotta make sure boys and girls in those communities are loved and cherished and nurtured and invested in." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1444: b'"What doesn\'t make sense is treating entire neighborhoods as danger zones." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1445: b'"We recognize that every child deserves opportunity. Not just some. Not just our own." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1446: b'"One study found that for every dollar we invest in Pre-K, we save at least twice that in reduced crime." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1447: b'"If we make investments early in our children, we will reduce the need to incarcerate those kids." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1448: b'"I believe crime is like any other epidemic\xe2\x80\x94we need to stop it before it starts." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1449: b'"For the first time in 40 years, America\'s crime rate and incarceration rate went down at the same time." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1450: b'"This is a cause that is bringing people in both houses of Congress together." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1451: b'"Mass incarceration makes our country worse off\xe2\x80\x94and we need to do something about it." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1452: b'"Our criminal justice system isn\'t as smart as it should be." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1453: b'"Our nation is being robbed of men and women who could be workers and taxpayers." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1454: b'"Around one million fathers are behind bars. Around one in nine African-American kids has a parent in prison." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1455: b'"African Americans are more likely to be arrested. They are more likely to be sentenced to more time for the same crime." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1456: b'"A growing body of research shows that people of color are more likely to be frisked, stopped, questioned, detained." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1457: b'"African Americans and Latinos make up 30 percent of our population. They make up 60 percent of our inmates." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1458: b'"Roughly one-third of the Justice Department\'s budget now goes toward incarceration." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1459: b'"For $80 billion we could double the salary of every high school teacher in America." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1460: b'"Every year, we spend $80 billion to keep those folks incarcerated." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1461: b'"In far too many cases the punishment does not fit the crime." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1462: b'"Over the last few decades, we\'ve locked up more and more nonviolent drug offenders for longer than ever before." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1463: b'"If we\'re going to deal with this problem, and the inequities involved, we\'re going to have to speak honestly." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1464: b'"Our prison population has doubled in the last two decades alone." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1465: b'"In 1980, there were 500,000 people behind bars in America ... Today, there are 2.2 million." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1466: b'"The United States is home to 5 percent of the world\'s population, but 25 percent of the world\'s prisoners." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1467: b'"In too many cases our criminal justice system becomes a pipeline from underfunded schools to overcrowded jails." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1468: b'"There is a long history of inequity in the criminal justice system in America." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1469: b'"We can\'t be satisfied\xe2\x80\x94are not satisfied\xe2\x80\x94until the opportunity gap is closed for everybody in America." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #NAACP106'
Text.1470: b'"Health care is not a privilege for the few, but a right for all of us." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1471: b'"We made progress, but our work is not done." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama #NAACP106'
Text.1472: b'"I would not be here and so many others would not be here without the NAACP." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
Text.1473: b'"Let\'s get something out of the way up front: I am not singing today." \xe2\x80\x94President Obama'
